Maxima made her way to Mt. St. Hilary. 

As soon as she arrived, she landed at the base of the mountain. The volcano 
was now dormant. Which was a good thing. 

She glanced about, making sure no one was around. As well as scouting the 
terrain. It was slightly different than in the late 20th & early 21st 
centuries. But.. nonetheless, this was the spot. 

She strode forward & made her way into a cavern, small at the moment, that 
would eventually serve as the main enterance. 

It was truly odd to just waltz right in on the Ark. She was use to the fact 
that there were heavy defenses in the area. Ahhh.. the good old days. It was 
something she missed. She smiled at the memory. 

Trudging further into the cavern, she soon enough came to the ark itself. 

Stopping a moment, she gazed. She was so close. 

Moving further as she soon enough entered the Ark. 

The light was barely there, using her animal like senses, she made her way to 
the Teletran console. Not as crafty as old Wheeljack or Ratchet, who knew 
Teletran well enough... she still needed to find a way to boost this place. 

Sensing the bodies everywhere, it nearly sickened her. But, she toughened up 
quickly enough as she reached Teletran 1. 

Sensing her way around, she fiddled with the console, trying to find out 
which fuse or switch or whatever would help to kick on the infrared or the 
photon lights all together. 

After a little tinkering, the lights flickered, then came on. She smiled, 
&quot;Success.&quot; 

She continued to tinker with Teletran 1, seeing what she could do to 
partially put it back online. Defenses were important. As much as she hated 
the Autobots, she could care less about the Autobot inhabitants,... but it 
was her Decepticon comrades she was more concerned with. 

After a little time, Teletran 1 came up partially. Blinking on, then tried to 
speak, &quot;Welco-...Dang-...Intrud-....Urgg-- Yaw-... Wuurrr-... Gggirrr-...&quot; 

Glancing up at the huge viewscreen as the screen flickered, then glancing 
back & focusing on the task as she hot wired & spliced, doing the best she 
could with the little resources she had. 

Finally... &quot;Searching.... Systems online... Defenses down...&quot; in that 
familiar voice. 

She got up & faced Teletran 1. 

&quot;Orders..&quot; it asked. 

She leaned over & started to type up a few things. &quot;Current orders: secure 
perimeter. Full defense systems online. Leave repair systems offline & none 
functioning. Repair to be done only manually. Outer defense systems at full, 
inner sentinel systems at maximum.&quot; as she continued to type. 

Then uplinked to Teletran 1. &quot;Uploading information data.&quot; 

After a couple minutes... &quot;Data received.&quot; 

She glanced back as she disconnected herself from Teletran 1, to see the 
dormant Autobots & Decepticons. It nearly tore her as she saw her comrades, 
broken & damage... in total stasis & offline. All those millions of years, 
she wondered about them, what happened to them, where they had gone. The pain 
of not knowing their fate... now.. she knew. 

&quot;Teletran... leave current forms in master control room/bridge untouched.&quot;

&quot;Acknowledged.&quot; the voice of the great computer stated. 

She went on with her supposed new duties here. This.. would be her home for a 
while. It was what she wanted to do when she awoke on Cybertron & came here. 
Somehow... she felt she had to be here. 

&quot;Teletran.. locate materials: Cybertonium, transparasteel, hydronium... &quot; she 
rambled off many metals & other things. 

&quot;Confirmed. Location: in the main hold. All materials there.&quot; Teletran 
confirmed. 

&quot;Good.&quot; 

She started to make her way from Teletran 1, as she stopped dead in her 
tracks. Her crimson optics fell upon Megatron. Propped up in a chair, 
dormant... he had fallen there when the Ark crashed on Earth. Her optics 
stared at him for the longest time. All time seemed to have melted, not 
knowing how long she watched her former Leader. How she honestly missed him. 

She brought herself out of the trance. Then made her way out of the Master 
Control Room. Her optics glanced at Megatron once more as she left.. heading 
down to the Main Hold.

